        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Would be happy to look into it and submit a PR\n\nvim/nvim calls the \"cursor check\" function(s) too often. Long ago I removed a couple calls in normal.c and saw a huge improvement with cursor movement performance. I would start there.\n\nI also think we should support (maybe optionally, idk) deferring layout/viewport updates during cursor movement, just allow the screen to be \"imperfect\" (stale highlights) while user is moving the cursor, and update only once every ~300ms.",
